FuncDef: This command disconnects a user from a session.
CLIs: disconnect [ address <ip-address> | session-id <session-id> | username <user-name> | { console | bluetooth | telnet | ftp | ssh | netconf | grpc } ]

ParaDef.Info: Specifies the IP address to disconnect, specified in dotted decimal notation. Values-ipv4-address |a.b.c.d, ipv6-address |x:x:x:x:x:x:x:x (eight 16-bit pieces), |x:x:x:x:x:x:d.d.d.d, |x - [0 to FFFF]H, |d - [0 to 255]D.
The model-driven session ID. Can be obtained using the show system management-interface datastore-locks [detail] command.
Specifies the name of the user. The name can be up to 32 characters.
